SIMPLE: oily
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oily
<hw>Oil"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Oilier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Oiliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting of oil;
containing oil; having the nature or qualities of oil; unctuous;
oleaginous; <as>as, <ex>oily</ex> matter or substance</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Covered with oil; greasy; hence, resembling oil;
<as>as, an <ex>oily</ex> appearance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Smoothly subservient; supple; compliant; plausible;
insinuating.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧This <xex>oily</xex> rascal.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>oily</qex> compliance in all alterations.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oily grain</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the
sesame.</cd> -- <col><b>Oily palm</b></col>, <cd>the oil
palm.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oinement</ent>⟦br⟧
